name: dw256A
description:
Unfolding of a dw256A sparse matrix into a lattice. The original matrix describes a problem in electromagnetics and is first documented by H. Dong in 1993. In this simulation, the matrix is represented as a lattice with 512 nodes which undergoes a process of unfolding until it reaches equilibrium. 

@lukapiskorec, mp4, 1000 x 1000 pix, 400 frames
